# CVE-2023-45853 - MiniZip integer overflow in zipOpenNewFileInZip4_64
# STATUS: False Positive (Debian Security Tracker: "ignored")
# REASON: contrib/minizip is NOT compiled into Debian's zlib1g binary package.
#         The zlib source tree contains the code, but the deployed binary does not.
#         NVD confirms: "MiniZip is not a supported part of the zlib product".
# REFS:   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2023-45853
#         https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-45853
#         https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy/discussions/6722
# REVIEW: Remove when base image upgrades to Debian Trixie (zlib1g 1:1.3+).
CVE-2023-45853 exp:2026-10-17

# CVE-2026-33845 - GnuTLS DTLS zero-length fragment DoS
# STATUS: Not Affected (vendor-tracker: unfixed in Debian Bookworm)
# REASON: Backend stack = Node 24 + OpenSSL. Keine GnuTLS/DTLS/WebRTC-
#         Dependency in package.json (verifiziert via grep über alle
#         workspace package.json-Files). libgnutls30 ist transitive
#         Debian-Layer (apt, util-linux) und wird vom Application-Code
#         nicht aufgerufen. DTLS-Angriffsvektor (UDP-basierter TLS-
#         Handshake) existiert in unserem Threat-Model nicht: kein
#         WebRTC, kein VoIP/SIP, kein QUIC, kein UDP-Service exposed.
# REFS:   https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-33845
#         https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-33845
# REVIEW: Entfernen sobald Debian Bookworm den Patch backportet ODER
#         Base-Image-Upgrade auf Debian Trixie.
CVE-2026-33845 exp:2026-08-06
